{% block title %}
   Canals and Narrow Straits
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        Geographical features that can help or hinder sea movement, depending upon who controls them
    </div>
    <ul>
        <li>
             Control of the land territories surrounding these features gives the controlling power and its allies the ability to travel through them while denying access to enemy powers
        </li>
        <li>Canals do not block land movement</li>
        <li>Narrow Straits cannot be crossed by land units</li>
        <li>If a canal or narrow strait is controlled by a power not on your side, but with which you are not yet at war, you must ask permission to use it, which may be denied</li>
